B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                     FY 2025        FY 2026           FY 2027
Title: Resilient Supply-and-Demand Networks (RSDN)                                                                                         15.545             -                 -
Description: The Resilient Supply-and-Demand Networks (RSDN) program is developing supply-chain risk management
analytics to detect systemic challenges and improve resilience in supply and demand networks (SDN). At present, the separation
of supply-chain information into confidential silos obscures a system-wide view, inhibiting comprehensive risk-focused analysis of
supply and demand networks. RSDN is developing techniques for modeling and stress-testing real-world SDNs, including network
analytics and visualizations, to reveal emerging fragilities and enable deep situational awareness of systemic risks and potential
disruptions. An RSDN stress-testing framework enables repeatable scenario analysis of strategic issues in supply and demand
networks, automated analysis and discovery of risk patterns, and evaluation of alternative risk mitigation strategies.

Beginning in FY 2026, this program will be funded in PE 0603467E, Project DAT-01.

Title: Defense Applications of Innovative Remote Sensing (DAIRS)                                                                              14.400             -                 -
Description: The Defense Applications of Innovative Remote Sensing (DAIRS) program was intended to enable new approaches
for the persistent long-range tracking of maritime and air targets. Specifically, DAIRS focused on the use of surface wave over-
the-horizon radar (SWOTHR) with operation in low latitudes. The program explored passive remote sensing using endemic noise
sources as a highly disruptive method for environmental and target sensing. A variety of processing and sensing techniques
provided the baseline technologies for clutter rejection, and this program combined those techniques with technologies to uncover

                                                                                                                                   TECHNOLOGY

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                        FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
spatial-temporal correlation, to try to suppress spread-Doppler clutter. The program investigated these methods for various
conditions that affect SWOTHR, including the day/night cycle, sea state, forward scatter and backscatter, and bistatic range.
Additionally, the program took a first-principles approach for classifying high frequency wavelengths for total disruption of the field.

