A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Strategic Mission Planning and Execution System (SMPES) will be the U.S. Air Force (USAF) and U.S. strategic nuclear forces' principal nuclear planning and analysis
tool for accessing consequence analysis information and strategic deterrence. SMPES consolidates the following six independently managed programs into one system:
1) Mission Planning and Analysis System (MPAS); 2) Global Adaptive Planning Collaborative Information Environment (GAP-CIE); 3) Decision Support Service (DSS)
- Nuclear Command and Control (NC2) Conference Module; 4) Nuclear Planning and Execution System Recapitalization (NPES Recap); 5) Force Status Readiness
(FSR); and 6) Force Survivability Analysis and Management (FSAM).

